OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775758265
OL,3,CArtemis crew share stories of lifelong
OL,4,Cbonds, tears shed and fears of re-entry
OL,6,FAs the crew of Artemis II hurtled home
OL,7,Ffrom the moon, they reflected on how
OL,8,Ftheir journey changed their
OL,9,Fperspective on life, as well as their
OL,10,Fanxieties about re-entering the
OL,11,FEarth's atmosphere.
OL,13,FJust days away from the end of their
OL,14,Fmission, the Artemis II crew carried
OL,15,Fout a press interview from space, with
OL,16,Fthe astronauts answering questions
OL,17,Fwith their floating microphone.
OL,19,FThey spoke about the bonds they had
OL,20,Fforged during the runup to the mission
OL,21,Fand how they had solidified in space.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775758265
OL,3,CArtemis crew share stories of lifelong
OL,4,Cbonds, tears shed and fears of re-entry
OL,6,FThe most poignant moment came when
OL,7,FCanadian astronaut Jeremy Hansen
OL,8,Fsuggested to his other crew mates that
OL,9,Fthey name a small crater on the moon
OL,10,Fafter Commander Reid Wiseman's late
OL,11,Fwife, Carroll.
OL,13,FThe moment was so charged with emotion
OL,14,Fthat Wiseman was too emotional to talk
OL,15,Fas they announced it.
OL,17,FCarroll Wiseman, a neonatal nurse,
OL,18,Fdied of cancer in 2020.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775758265
OL,3,CArtemis crew share stories of lifelong
OL,4,Cbonds, tears shed and fears of re-entry
OL,6,F"Just for me personally, that was kind
OL,7,Fof the pinnacle moment of the mission
OL,8,Ffor me," Wiseman said from space on
OL,9,FWednesday night.
OL,11,FHe said when it was read out, everyone
OL,12,Fon board the capsule was crying.
OL,14,F"That was, I think, where the four of
OL,15,Fus were the most forged, the most
OL,16,Fbonded."
OL,18,FThe crew also decided to name another
OL,19,Fcrater after their capsule, Integrity.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775758265
OL,3,CArtemis crew share stories of lifelong
OL,4,Cbonds, tears shed and fears of re-entry
OL,6,FThe decision also called back to
OL,7,Fearlier trips to the moon. During
OL,8,FApollo 8 in 1968, astronaut Jim Lovell
OL,9,Fbestowed his wife's name upon a
OL,10,Fprominent lunar peak: Mount Marilyn.
OL,12,FThe three Americans and one Canadian
OL,13,Fof Artemis II are the first lunar
OL,14,Fvisitors since Apollo 17 closed out
OL,15,Fthat grand epoch in 1972, and their
OL,16,Fcrater-naming request temporarily left
OL,17,Fground controllers speechless.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
